        for &lt;XXXXXX&gt;
        (version=TLS1_2 cipher=ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256 bits=128&#x2F;128);
        Mon, 03 Feb 2020 08:37:30 -0800 (PST)

[Nitpick] Instead of this:<p><pre><code>    ;(async function () {
      try {
        &#x2F;&#x2F; All your code
      } catch (e) {
        console.log(e)
      }
    })()
</code></pre>
Just do this:<p><pre><code>    ;(async function () {
      &#x2F;&#x2F; All your code
    })().catch(console.error)
</code></pre>
Overuse of try&#x2F;catch is probably the #1 mistake I see when people use async&#x2F;await.
